# Intuition
Each score must be tracked. Remember that every time a player scores a 10, the next two rounds have a multiplier of two.

# Approach
Create three variables for each player. One of which is a tick that counts down the two days where the multiplier is active for that player. Make sure that if a player scores a 10, the tick is set to 2 and the multiplier is set to 2. For each iteration, make sure 1 is subtracted from the tick as long as it is greater than 0. Once the tick hits 0, set the multiplier back to 1.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)

- Space complexity:
O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int isWinner(int[] player1, int[] player2) {
        int multi1 = 1;
        int multi2 = 1;
        int tick1 = 0;
        int tick2 = 0;
        int total1 = 0;
        int total2 = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < player1.length; i++)
        {
            total1 += player1[i] * multi1;
            total2 += player2[i] * multi2;
            if (tick1 == 0)
                multi1 = 1;
            if (tick2 == 0)
                multi2 = 1;

            if (player1[i] == 10)
            {
                tick1 = 2;
                multi1 = 2;
            }
            if (player2[i] == 10)
            {
                tick2 = 2;
                multi2 = 2;
            }

            if (tick1 > 0)
                tick1--;
            if (tick2 > 0)
                tick2--;
        }

        if (total1 > total2)
            return 1;
        else if (total2 > total1)
            return 2;
        else
            return 0;

    }
}
```

