# Approach
n will be the size of the array given

Then if first number is 10 for player1 then we can say that we have a lastTen for him/her. By lastTen I mean if he/she has any last 2 scores as 10. 

Then we will have 2 variables for storing the scores of the two players, if lastTen is 1 then we will add 1 and multiply the current score and then add to total, else if lastTen is 0 then after adding 1 it will be 1 only, so the score will be take care of itself.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)

- Space complexity: O(1)

